<br>
Actually, that's the story exactly as I represented it.  Please re-read what I posted.  I did leave out one detail.  The first part of this occurred right before 3:00 a.m. (2:45 a.m.) Pacific, right before the 4 hour patch.  I set my alarm, hoping that no one would be there that early and that maybe Dyllin would respawn.  I get up and get on at 7:03 a.m., 3 minutes after the server went up (presumably).  Shewina was already there.  You told me I should have &quot;got in line&quot;.  That was exactly what I intended to do, but each time I tried, Shewina was there.  I know that your guild acquired at least one and maybe two more pages in the intervening time.<br>
<br>
Nonetheless, the guild, or at least Krystallgold, adhered to their (or her) word and let me take the site, and I successfully completed the quest.<br>
<br>
Whether your guild is farming this item or not has yet to be determined.  It does leave some troubling questions unanswered.<br>
<br>
For example, why, after I gave Shewina and Krystallgold the page, did Shewina stay?<br>
<br>
Why was she there first thing in the morning, after I'd given her what she was putatively after?<br>
<br>
Exactly how many Testaments of Vanear did she need?<br>
<br>
Why, when I ran into Krystallgold later, didn't she have a Testament, when she was the one who I had given the page to (and, later, she told me she hadn't gotten one yet, and if anyone deserves one, she does)?  I was led to believe that Krystallgold was the &quot;friend&quot; Shewina was waiting for, but apparently not.<br>
<br>
Here's an interesting link: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.guildsay.com/boards/view_thread.php?id=5834&type=g&board=310">www.guildsay.com/boards/v...&board=310</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  I think &quot;Kimmz&quot; response about how this isn't farming because of Firiona Vie's Trivial Loot Code is very telling about their attitude about this.<br>
<br>
Lastly, &quot;defamation&quot; and &quot;libel&quot; only stick when the charges are untrue.  I'm reporting the truth, as I know it to be.  Even your account of what occured is in line with my account here.  You admit they've &quot;held the camp for a few days&quot;.  And, according to your words on your guild's message board, this isn't about who's right but about &quot;damage control&quot;.  Spin control.  There's no substantial disagreement about the facts about what happened.<br>
<br>
I'm sorry if you and your guild look bad, but it's not my behavior that's making them look bad.  It's their own behavior.  If they were honorable, then their actions should speak well of them and here they most definitely do not (or, as my mother used to tell me, don't do anything you don't want on the Six O'Clock News).  They only have themselves to blame for the &quot;pr problem&quot;, as you put it on your guild's message board.<br>
