That said, if a monk is continually camping the Dyllin spawn, and if said monk is too high to even fight Dyllin.. said monk should leave.  I can't quite figure out what level she is, but the other link was almost indicative that she was waiting on others because she can't fight him without trivial'ing him. So she's acting ONLY as a placeholder camper, which is just wrong on a camp that's highly desirably by a lot of folks.<br>
<br>
I'm wondering.. if the claimant died while first originally killing Dyllin ... why didn't she help him? Did she enjoy his death, since he'd gotten Dyllin?  That part bothered me... if she was afk/asleep, not trying to respond (a simply /boggle would count as a response if you cannot understand it) ... then the camp is not really hers. It's part of the &quot;you snooze, you lose&quot; deal, unfortunately.<br>
<br>
The claimant also returned the page.. that was highly impressive.   There's 2 actions after that that are acceptable.  1. leave the camp, having obtained what was desired 2. return the page, with a little note saying &quot;hey, we are trying to get several of these, so I dont' feel right about keeping this one&quot; ...  <br>
<br>
Keeping it, while continuing the camp, is just cheap.<br>
